value.string: Purpose: Read Location ID Values from a data table
cvControlRoomURL - Used in process to know which control room we are connected to

cvEnvironment - Variable used to know if we are in the TEST, QA or PROD environment. If variable is passed, process was called from another process.  If variable is not passed, then we are testing locally.
cvLogFilePath - Variable for the path to a local log file in case there is an error.
cvLogLevel - Variable to hold the log level code, DEBUG, ERROR, FATAL, INFO or WARN.
tblLocationIds - the data table containing the location ID info
NOTE:  This process will not stop execution when an error occurs.  It is up to the calling client to handle the error, as they see fit.  This process will log the error to the log file
vErrorString - Variable passed back to the calling program with the error message for data validation and connection errors
Local File Unit Testing - Gather the environment variables, assign input variables
Steps For Local Testing Variable Assignment
Write to the log file (do this after the testing section, to allow for assignment of cv variables)
Search data table to assign a list of row,column coordinates for each matching location ID
Count the number of entries in lstLocationIDs to determine how many rows in the data table matched the location ID
If there is exactly 1 match, extract the set of row,column coordinates for the matching location ID
Split the strRowColumn string (row,column), to be able to get the row [0] for the matching location ID
Assign the values for the matching location ID to variables
Convert to number type values for use with Terminal Emulator actions
If there is not exactly 1 match, error out
